Dry springs were hence an important factor during the hottest Dust Bowl summers of 1934 and 1936 (Cowan et al., 2017).
However, the role of SSTs in spring drought specifically is less than clear (Donat et al., 2016), as are the driving mechanisms
of high decadal heat wave activity overall.
Could such heat waves occur again, possibly stronger due to global warming? In order to better understand and quantify
the risk of recurrence, or strengthening, of such the damaging heat and drought events we need to better quantify the contri-
bution by SSTs, random and unpredictable atmospheric variability, land surface feedbacks, and land management.
